topics.body:
"@uc9":/dis/the-time-wasting-thread/post/5328a7ac6368723f486e0000#post_5328a7ac6368723f486e0000
!http://i1.kym-cdn.com/photos/images/newsfeed/000/703/501/d16.jpg!

I saw a video of a medic getting shot while he was tending to an injured opposition fighter. Shooting at you own civilians when they’re down… Just... Why?. It makes sense to me why these people want to distance themselves from Russia. The Ukraine was behind the Iron Curtain for the better part of a century, and Ukrainians want to form a relationship with Western Nations that were either never part of the USSR or became independent after its collapse. They’re pushing for change, but they get bullets in response…and I’m not saying Russians are bad or that they’re still harsh communists (although there is still a communist party). I’m just saying that I can understand why a country’s people wouldn’t want to be associated with a government that was oppressing them just over 20 years prior.

This is getting into madness.
